      <div class="thumb-headline thumb-headline-bottom">
        <div class="thumb-h">Stanley almost killed its best product, then re-pointed the same 1913 cup at a buyer its dashboards were not counting.</div>
        <p class="body-text">The Quencher buyer was a woman drinking water at her desk all day, not the outdoorsman the firm had been built around since 1913.</p>
        <p class="source">Stanley revenue trajectory, 2018 to 2024 (BusinessOfFashion, WSJ).</p>
