    <div class="say">Reveal each strategy in order. Concentrated picks one segment and serves it deeply. Porsche on the sports-car enthusiast, a campus food truck on late-night vegan ramen, Liquid Death's 2018 entry. The tight focus pays off when the segment is right. It sinks you when the segment moves because there is nowhere to fall back to. Differentiated serves several segments at once, each with its own offer, accepting the cost of parallel product lines because the scale recoups it. GM's 1920s Sloan ladder of Chevrolet to Cadillac, P&amp;G's laundry portfolio. Undifferentiated goes after everyone with one offer. Ford's Model T, Coca-Cola Classic. Rare in 2026 because a focused rival picks off the most profitable buyers. The chooser between the three is arithmetic, not principle. As buyer differences grow and tailoring gets cheaper, the answer shifts.</div>
